This project uses Tailwind CSS for styling with specific conventions:

## Utility Patterns

1. Use `cn()` utility from `lib/utils` for conditional class merging
2. Prefer semantic class grouping (layout → spacing → colors → etc.)
3. Use Tailwind's built-in color system with custom theme colors:
   - `primary`: Primary brand color
   - `muted`: Muted/secondary colors

## Common Classes

Frequently used class combinations:
- Layout: `flex flex-col gap-{size}`
- Text: `text-{size} font-bold text-primary`
- Containers: `w-full rounded bg-muted p-{size}`
- Lists: `flex flex-col gap-{size} list-disc pl-{size}`

## Best Practices

1. Use semantic class names when extending components
2. Maintain consistent spacing scales
3. Follow mobile-first responsive design
4. Use Tailwind's color opacity modifiers when needed
5. Leverage CSS variables for theme customization
